h3. Issue Summary
As per the title, if you attempt to run a Pipelines build manually, you will see the following error message, in case you are using Safari:
{code}
An unidentified error occurred. Please try again.
{code}

The build will execute just fine, but the error will always show up.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Log in to Bitbucket using Safari;
 # Navigate to any repository that has a valid bitbucket-pipelines.yml configuration in it;
 # Click on the Pipelines tab > Run Pipelines;
 # Run any Pipelines build;
 # You will see the following error message
{code}
An unidentified error occurred. Please try again.
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The Pipelines build will execute normally, without any error messages showing up in the UI

h3. Actual Results
The below exception is thrown:
{noformat}
An unidentified error occurred. Please try again.
{noformat}

h3. Workaround

Use either Chrome or Firefox, which don't have this error message, or ignore the error message altogether.

h3. Summary: If there's a Workspace, which has more then 100 users and we would like to get the list of users via the API, multiple API calls needs to be done as the maximum pagelen is 100. 

h3. Actual results:
Multiple API calls needs to be done, for example:

{code:java}
curl --request GET --url 'https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/workspaces/workspaceID/members?pagelen=100' --user username:apppassword
curl --request GET --url 'https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/workspaces/workspaceID/members?pagelen=100&page=2' --user username:apppassword
curl --request GET --url 'https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/workspaces/workspaceID/members?pagelen=100&page=3' --user username:apppassword
{code}


h3. Expected results:
Being able to have a larger pagelen (for example 1000)

{code:java}
curl --request GET --url 'https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/workspaces/workspaceID/members?pagelen=1000' --user username:apppassword
{code}
